Key Points: 
 
As an NHS organisation the only pay elements we have that fall under the bonus pay 
criteria  are  distinction  award  (Staff  grade  and  associate  specialist)  and  clinical 
excellence  awards  (consultants)  which  are  only  applicable  to  certain  groups  of 
medical staff.  
 
As  with  the  median  hourly  rate  of  pay,  this  is  based  on  the  mid-point  of  all  staff 
receiving bonus pay.  
 

