Key Points: 
 
This calculation expresses the number of staff receiving bonus pay as a percentage 
of the total number of staff in each gender group.  
 
Only certain medical staff receive pay that is classified as bonus pay. This group has 
a  significantly  different  gender  split  when  compared  to  the  Trust  as  a  whole.  The 
relevance  of  this  indicator  for  our  organisation  is  less  significant  as  bonus  pay 
applies to less than 7% percent of all staff employed.  
 
