Key Points:  
 
In  order  to  create  the  quartile  information  all  staff  are  sorted  by  their  hourly  rate  of 
pay, this list is then split into four equal parts (where possible).  
 
When reviewing the quartile information it is important to take into account the types 
of  roles  available  within  the  organisation  and  the  different  gender  splits  that  occur 
within specific roles.  
 
The highest variances for the quartiles when compared to the overall Trust value are 
in the lower, lower middle and upper middle quartiles. It is these quartiles which have 
the most pronounced gender split, where female staff are the predominant majority. 

