This is driving the mean and median pay differences. Included in the lower quartiles 
for instance are administrative & ancillary staff groups, such as Health Care Support 
Workers that traditionally have attracted a higher proportion of female staff.  
 
The  upper  quartile  has  a  lower  proportion  of  female  staff  than  the  other  three 
quartiles. The variance in this quartile is mainly due to significantly different gender 
splits in medical staffing and senior managerial roles in the Trust. 
 

